1
00:00:01,610 --> 00:00:03,510
(Episode 16)

2
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,850
Look here, Ms. Ma.

3
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:09,980
He is...

4
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:18,160
Are you kidding me, Ms. Ma?

5
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:23,960
All that laughing
brought tears to my eyes.

6
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:26,560
How is this something
to laugh about?

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,670
I guess it's not,

8
00:00:29,330 --> 00:00:31,900
but it's so ridiculous
that I can't help it.

9
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:38,140
He was...

10
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,950
the postmaster
at my old workplace...

11
00:00:40,950 --> 00:00:42,610
before I got married.

12
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:44,720
After his daughter gave birth,

13
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:46,650
she stayed with her parents
for postnatal care.

14
00:00:46,650 --> 00:00:48,490
The whole family was
at the hotel to relax,

15
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:50,890
and I was on my way up
to greet them all.

16
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:54,890
His daughter's name
is Park Soo Yeon.

17
00:00:54,890 --> 00:00:56,560
Confirm it if you don't believe me.

18
00:00:57,430 --> 00:01:00,000
Room 1512, Park Soo Yeon.

19
00:01:00,730 --> 00:01:02,170
The reservation is probably
under her name.

20
00:01:03,870 --> 00:01:05,740
Then, why were you
talking about money?

21
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:08,010
Money?

22
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:11,580
Let me know if you need more money.

23
00:01:12,010 --> 00:01:13,550
I'll try to make it happen again.

24
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:16,950
I'm grateful enough
for your assistance before.

25
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:18,750
It's not like we're strangers.

26
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:21,650
How else can I help you
if not with your financial problems?

27
00:01:22,390 --> 00:01:24,090
You're the best.

28
00:01:25,990 --> 00:01:28,990
I needed money
when taking over the brewery,

29
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:30,730
and the postmaster granted my loan.

30
00:01:31,330 --> 00:01:32,900
He knows my situation,

31
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:36,030
so that was him offering
to help out again.

32
00:01:36,670 --> 00:01:37,670
Are you happy now?

33
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:40,810
I don't know why
I need to explain myself like this,

34
00:01:41,470 --> 00:01:45,010
but now that I
have explained it all,

35
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:47,850
whether you think of me
as a gold digger or not...

36
00:01:48,510 --> 00:01:50,080
is entirely...

37
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,220
up to you.

38
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:08,000
(Somang Hall)

39
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,940
I never thought
I'd be treated like this.

40
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:18,240
What does he take me for?

41
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:21,680
(Eagle Brewery)

42
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,710
Darn, that hurts.

43
00:02:49,070 --> 00:02:50,070
Yes, sir.

44
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:51,440
It's me, Mr. Park.

45
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,280
Well,

46
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:56,650
I'd like you to look into something.

47
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:01,520
I don't care if he's a chairman.

48
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:04,090
He has no right
calling me a gold digger.

49
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:06,260
Unbelievable.

50
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:08,030
It frustrates me
the more I think about it.

51
00:03:09,130 --> 00:03:11,560
Contract or no contract,
I should've slapped him...

52
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:13,200
across the face.

53
00:03:20,940 --> 00:03:22,210
Hello. Ok Bun, is it?

54
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,480
Are you free to talk?

55
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:25,940
Of course.

56
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:28,650
Do you have new evidence?

57
00:03:29,050 --> 00:03:31,750
The private detective is gathering
whatever information he can...

58
00:03:31,750 --> 00:03:34,050
from the neighborhood
where Ms. Kim...

59
00:03:34,050 --> 00:03:35,920
ran her piano academy ten years ago.

60
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:38,120
I'm sure
we'll get good news pretty soon.

61
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:42,290
Could the photo we saw
have been fabricated?

62
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,530
Ms. Ma, come on.

63
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:47,430
Who'd bother to fabricate
such a photo?

64
00:03:48,230 --> 00:03:50,300
Oh, right. That reminds me.

65
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:54,470
I even saw the little girl
that's most likely her daughter.

66
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:55,770
Really?

67
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:59,280
We'll soon have heaps
of irrefutable evidence.

68
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,250
How dare she try to fool
my brother-in-law?

69
00:04:01,810 --> 00:04:04,420
If this is true,
I won't let it slide.

70
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:06,950
I'll teach her a lesson
in a way that'll shut her up!

71
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:10,890
It seems as though
you and I see eye to eye.

72
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:12,990
Can I call you Kwang Sook
from now on?

73
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:15,890
Sure thing, Kwang Sook.

74
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:20,930
I'll call you again
once I have more to tell you.

75
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:24,400
Sure. Have a good day.

76
00:04:27,210 --> 00:04:28,640
You're here.

77
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:31,080
I heard you quit
the Zumba dance class.

78
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,740
Oh, that.

79
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,580
I'm busy at the salon
and have too much to do.

80
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,750
That's just one of many reasons.

81
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:40,150
In fact, it's not like
you have any weight to lose.

82
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:41,690
Oh, please.

83
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,550
All right.

84
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:46,490
How was the rummage sale?

85
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:49,960
I set one up to raise money
for volunteer work at the prison,

86
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:53,300
and many people participated
since it was for a good cause.

87
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,100
You volunteer even at a prison?

88
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:57,970
I do. Once a month.

89
00:04:58,840 --> 00:04:59,870
That reminds me.

90
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:02,510
While volunteering
at Uijeongbu Prison last week,

91
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,940
I ran into Ms. Kim.

92
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:06,680
Ms. Kim who runs the piano academy?

93
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,710
That's right.

94
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:11,050
Her friend must've been
falsely imprisoned.

95
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:13,150
She was on her way out
from visiting,

96
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:14,920
and she must've cried
her eyes out...

97
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,790
because her eyes were bloodshot.

98
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:18,960
They were like those of a rabbit.

99
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:19,960
Wait.

100
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:22,690
I'll be right back
after making a quick phone call.

101
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:23,760
Okay.

102
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,540
- Hello?
- It's me, Detective.

103
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:34,840
Please look into Uijeongbu Prison.

104
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,880
It seems like someone important
related to Ms. Kim...

105
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:39,680
is imprisoned there.

106
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,090
It's unbelievable.

107
00:05:48,490 --> 00:05:51,190
Not only did she
sponge off Chun Soo,

108
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:53,930
but she even cheated on him.

109
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:56,290
And yet she held her head high
and raised her voice?

110
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:00,830
She's not our sister-in-law,
and she's not even a human being.

111
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,930
I also found it hard
to believe at first.

112
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:08,170
Anyway, it's Chun Soo
who's hurting the most right now.

113
00:06:08,340 --> 00:06:10,710
Let's be careful with what we say,
considering his situation.

114
00:06:12,110 --> 00:06:13,710
We shouldn't just sit back
and watch it like this.

115
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:15,150
What can we do about it?

116
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:17,980
- If I could, I'd just...
- What would you do?

117
00:06:19,620 --> 00:06:22,050
I'm just saying this
because I'm upset.

118
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,030
By the way,

119
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:31,960
she's the one at fault.

120
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:36,030
It's not right to divorce her
while giving her all the alimony.

121
00:06:36,170 --> 00:06:37,340
But there's Yeoung Ju.

122
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:47,080
To be honest, I have this suspicion.

123
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,920
Can we be sure that
Yeoung Ju is Chun Soo's daughter?

124
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:52,980
I don't believe a word she says.

125
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:53,990
- Come on!
- Come on!

126
00:06:53,990 --> 00:06:56,150
She suddenly showed up
and said she was pregnant.

127
00:06:56,150 --> 00:06:57,560
That's how they got married.

128
00:07:01,230 --> 00:07:02,230
I thought...

129
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:04,530
he'd marry Mi Sun.

130
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,500
- Mi Sun?
- Yes.

131
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,070
The two had always been together
since they were little, you know.

132
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,510
I thought they were just friends.

133
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:16,340
Was it in middle school
or high school?

134
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:18,880
I took a peek
at Chun Soo's diary one day.

135
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:21,350
He had a big crush on Mi Sun.

136
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,310
It was 30 years ago.

137
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,780
If Chun Soo had married Mi Sun,

138
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,890
he wouldn't have turned out
this way.

139
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:35,290
Chun Soo wouldn't act on
dark thoughts, would he?

140
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:36,330
Hey!

141
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,300
Why would you say that?

142
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:40,230
I don't think he would,

143
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:42,430
but he rarely expresses
his feelings...

144
00:07:42,430 --> 00:07:44,000
and often carries grudges.

145
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,340
So I'm a little worried
that he'd explode one day.

146
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:49,340
We should call him often.

147
00:07:50,110 --> 00:07:51,910
We should visit him a lot
and see how he's doing.

148
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:54,910
We should help him
unleash his emotional baggage.

149
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,280
That's the only thing we can do.

150
00:07:59,550 --> 00:08:00,990
Kang Soo, go ahead and unjinx it.

151
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:02,150
Say you take it back.

152
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,920
Go ahead and do it.

153
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,060
I take it back.

154
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,060
I haven't slept a wink...

155
00:08:09,330 --> 00:08:10,800
for the past three days.

156
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:12,530
For three days?

157
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:14,270
Yes.

158
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:16,570
I've been awake for three days.

159
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:19,670
I couldn't sleep even for a second.

160
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:23,710
Even when my eyelids get heavy
and I close my eyes,

161
00:08:24,910 --> 00:08:26,040
I can't fall asleep.

162
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:30,110
Have you been shocked
or stressed out recently?

163
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:34,850
I had a big fight...

164
00:08:35,990 --> 00:08:37,520
with my wife.

165
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:45,800
These are sleeping pills.

166
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,670
You can't increase the dosage
just because you can't fall asleep.

167
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:50,940
Take only 1 pill
30 minutes before going to bed.

168
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,170
Okay. I will.

169
00:08:59,310 --> 00:09:01,180
(Wife)

170
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,020
What's the matter?

171
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,320
Where are you?

172
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:09,520
Let's meet up.

173
00:09:09,850 --> 00:09:11,220
I have no reason to see you.

174
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,720
And I have nothing to say to you.

175
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:14,660
Come on, Chun Soo.

176
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:17,400
Don't leave Yeoung Ju alone.
You should go back to the States.

177
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:19,360
Do you want me to go back like this?

178
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,630
Without concluding anything?

179
00:09:21,830 --> 00:09:22,970
I told you.

180
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:25,370
I can't give you
the conclusion you want.

181
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,210
Do whatever you want in the States,
whether it's cheating or whatever.

182
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:31,080
I don't care.

183
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:33,780
But I will never get a divorce.

184
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,750
Being stubborn
won't resolve anything.

185
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,180
I'll keep paying for...

186
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,550
Yeoung Ju's tuition
and living expenses.

187
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:41,220
Just be a good mother to her.

188
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:44,020
There is nothing else
I want from you other than that.

189
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:03,840
Hello, Mr. Park.

190
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,810
Here's an update
on your instructions.

191
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:08,750
The person who reserved
Junior Suite Room 1512...

192
00:10:08,810 --> 00:10:10,010
is named Park Soo Yeon.

193
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,780
Three adults and a newborn baby
stayed in the room.

194
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,190
It seems like they were a family.

195
00:10:15,790 --> 00:10:16,850
Okay.

196
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:18,720
Thank you.

197
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,640
(Eagle Brewery Unrefined Makgeolli)

198
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,140
You're back.

199
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,310
- Nothing happened, right?
- No.

200
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:38,910
Oh, right. A visitor just came here
looking for you.

201
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,050
- A visitor?
- Yes.

202
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,410
Your mother took him to the annex.

203
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,430
Gosh.

204
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:02,530
I apologize for showing up
unannounced like this.

205
00:11:02,770 --> 00:11:04,770
You don't have to apologize.

206
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,070
You're always welcome.

207
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,270
My gosh.

208
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,240
Please drop the honorifics, Mother.

209
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,710
You can just think of me
as your son.

210
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:14,410
My son?

211
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:17,950
Did I go too far?

212
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:20,480
You are the youngest brother-in-law
of Dr. Lee.

213
00:11:20,850 --> 00:11:22,720
You are like my son.

214
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:26,020
Thank you for saying that.

215
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,560
I'll be your son for the time being,

216
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,760
but hopefully,

217
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:32,060
I'll soon become your son-in-law.

218
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:34,130
How sweet.

219
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:38,040
You sound
so straightforward and assertive.

220
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:39,900
Mother!

221
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:42,340
I'm home...

222
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:50,850
Mr. Park Sang Nam,
what are you doing here?

223
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:54,790
Why would you sound so tactless?

224
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:57,390
What do you think he's here for?

225
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:00,190
I came here to see you.

226
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:04,860
Can we talk outside?

227
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:07,360
If you have anything to say,
say it here.

228
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,470
Have a seat.

229
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:10,700
Come on out.

230
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:15,640
Please excuse me
for a second, Mother.

231
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:23,780
That darn brat!

232
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:28,190
(Live brightly, have a broad mind,
and have big hopes.)

233
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:36,690
You can't be unilateral like this.

234
00:12:37,530 --> 00:12:40,970
I made myself clear
that I didn't want to get remarried.

235
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,000
I made myself clear as well...

236
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,700
that I don't want to rush things,
so we can stay friends.

237
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:49,870
You just don't understand
what I'm saying.

238
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:53,040
I have no intention...

239
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,680
of being friends with you...

240
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,280
at all.

241
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:02,220
I will be friends with you
no matter what.

242
00:13:03,150 --> 00:13:04,220
What?

243
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:06,520
I figured it would be difficult...

244
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:09,260
to meet someone
as precious as you again.

245
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:11,660
I don't want to lose you.

246
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:13,830
I think you're mistaken.

247
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:16,630
I'm not the kind of person...

248
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:18,300
you think I am.

249
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:23,670
Your sincere feelings
for your late husband are precious.

250
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,340
And your hard work
to run the brewery...

251
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:28,310
of your husband is precious too.

252
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:32,180
You are a truly precious person
who is hard to find...

253
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:34,120
in today's world.

254
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:39,120
Whatever.

255
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:42,430
Please stop coming here
unannounced like this.

256
00:13:42,830 --> 00:13:43,860
It makes me uncomfortable.

257
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,760
If you keep being like this,

258
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:50,940
it will only make me
more enthusiastic.

259
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:53,340
What?

260
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:56,210
Since I was little,
I have had this habit...

261
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:58,410
of wanting to do something even more
when someone tells me not to.

262
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:02,250
You just lit a fire
of determination...

263
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,120
in the heart of Park Sang Nam.

264
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:08,920
My gosh.

265
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,390
I'm making dinner.

266
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:14,230
It's not much,
but stay for dinner, Sang Nam.

267
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:15,860
Mom!

268
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,560
What? Why?

269
00:14:19,530 --> 00:14:20,730
Please leave.

270
00:14:22,330 --> 00:14:23,870
It is impolite
to send away a guest...

271
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:26,440
who visited us during mealtime
without offering him a meal.

272
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,440
You can stay, can't you?

273
00:14:29,510 --> 00:14:31,040
Of course, I can.

274
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:32,440
Do you like doenjang jjigae?

275
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,210
I can't get enough of it.

276
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:37,210
We have similar tastes in food.

277
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,380
Mom!

278
00:14:38,650 --> 00:14:41,750
He's my guest,
so mind your own business.

279
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,290
It's not much,

280
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:45,120
but have dinner with me.

281
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,190
Sure, Mother!

282
00:14:52,630 --> 00:14:53,760
What's with them?

283
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,100
You're home.

284
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,470
Your dinner is ready, sir.

285
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,010
No. I don't feel like eating dinner.

286
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,470
Are you not feeling well?

287
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:05,580
I'm still kind of full from lunch.

288
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:07,280
Can you get me some headache pills?

289
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:08,680
Do you have a headache?

290
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,250
No, it's not bad. Thank you.

291
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:12,550
All right.

292
00:15:15,550 --> 00:15:18,790
The chairman
hasn't been feeling well lately.

293
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,260
You're right.

294
00:15:23,690 --> 00:15:24,760
Come in.

295
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:28,870
Some painkillers.

296
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:30,330
Yes, thanks.

297
00:15:34,740 --> 00:15:36,940
Are you having trouble at work?

298
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:39,010
No. Why?

299
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:41,910
You've been looking grumpy...

300
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:43,650
and a bit down recently.

301
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:46,720
Why would I have any trouble
at work?

302
00:15:47,150 --> 00:15:49,490
Nothing's wrong, so don't worry.

303
00:15:50,290 --> 00:15:51,460
Good, then.

304
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:54,730
I need to think
and would like to be alone.

305
00:15:54,890 --> 00:15:56,930
Okay. I'll let you rest.

306
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:08,140
I was too rash.

307
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:13,480
Why would someone as cautious...

308
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:15,280
and perfect as me make that mistake?

309
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:28,030
Welcome home.

310
00:16:28,660 --> 00:16:30,930
I trust you had a great day,

311
00:16:30,930 --> 00:16:32,900
- Chairman.
- Chairman.

312
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:38,900
This is what gives me
the will to live.

313
00:16:39,470 --> 00:16:43,310
I give it my all
in that battlefield called "work"...

314
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:46,240
for you and Se Ri.

315
00:16:47,040 --> 00:16:48,310
Do you know that?

316
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,910
I do.

317
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:52,980
You're in a good mood today.

318
00:16:53,420 --> 00:16:55,290
You bet I am.

319
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:57,720
Ta-da.

320
00:16:57,860 --> 00:16:58,890
(Sorabol's Moonlit Night)

321
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:00,360
Is that our new product?

322
00:17:00,760 --> 00:17:02,790
I rushed home
as soon as I got off...

323
00:17:02,790 --> 00:17:04,800
so you could have a taste.

324
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:07,430
Gather in the kitchen!

325
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:13,600
Your dad's on a high.

326
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,580
This is called...

327
00:17:18,580 --> 00:17:21,210
Sorabol's Moonlit Night.

328
00:17:22,210 --> 00:17:23,450
Here we go.

329
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:31,720
For you, Se Ri.

330
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:34,730
For my darling Mi Ae.

331
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:39,760
Sorabol's Moonlit Night.

332
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,670
Isn't it lovely?

333
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:43,330
- It is.
- It is.

334
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,780
What do you think?

335
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:53,940
It's nice and sweet.

336
00:17:55,180 --> 00:17:56,650
Right?

337
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:59,720
But I don't know makgeolli.

338
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:04,220
That's strange.

339
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:05,690
What is?

340
00:18:05,690 --> 00:18:08,330
It doesn't taste like
what you brought home last time.

341
00:18:09,930 --> 00:18:13,330
That was a working prototype.

342
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:16,700
We improved on that
and made this new product.

343
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,140
I prefer the other one.

344
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:21,000
What?

345
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:25,440
That tasted luxurious
without being sweet.

346
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:28,810
I don't think
the additives are mixed well.

347
00:18:29,010 --> 00:18:32,180
It's as if
all the ingredients are separate.

348
00:18:32,950 --> 00:18:35,720
You don't know enough
to criticize our product!

349
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:36,990
My gosh.

350
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,960
Why did you yell?

351
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,890
Your husband
slaved away all day long...

352
00:18:40,890 --> 00:18:42,960
and instead of stroking his ego,

353
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,560
all you think about...

354
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:46,900
is what you can do
to spend more money.

355
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,300
And you put me down!

356
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,700
What do you do all day long?

357
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,870
What do you do at home?

358
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:56,770
What got into you?

359
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:58,740
Mom. Stop it.

360
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:00,210
Calm down, Dad.

361
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:06,680
You ruined my mood.

362
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:09,720
Don't drink this!

363
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:13,890
What's wrong with him?

364
00:19:13,890 --> 00:19:16,760
What did I say
that got him so upset?

365
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:18,760
Don't.

366
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,300
My goodness.

367
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:28,070
I thought my ears would bleed.

368
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:38,020
These will suit Ha Ni perfectly.

369
00:19:41,850 --> 00:19:43,790
(Kimchi Jjigae and Pork Belly)

370
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:44,920
Goodbye.

371
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:48,390
I'm in a weird mood.

372
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:50,590
Can we go somewhere
for another drink?

373
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:52,230
Let's call it a day.

374
00:19:52,230 --> 00:19:53,430
I have to pick up Ha Ni.

375
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,930
I'm not in the mood for a drink.

376
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,840
Poor Chun Soo.

377
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:03,910
I can't handle the situation
unless I have another drink.

378
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,640
Let's have just one more.

379
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:09,550
Instead of making up excuses
to drink, go home.

380
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:11,450
You're so inconsiderate.

381
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:14,690
Don't call Chun Soo drunk
and say something weird.

382
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:17,220
He must be
distraught enough already.

383
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:19,320
How dare you?

384
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,990
I'm the older brother here.

385
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:24,060
You're always lecturing me.

386
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:25,900
I can tell what not to do.

387
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:30,930
I'm afraid to get married.

388
00:20:32,870 --> 00:20:35,670
Chun Soo and you too, Beom Soo.

389
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:37,110
Your marriages failed.

390
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:40,710
Who am I to meet, trust and marry?

391
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:42,710
There are people like Kwang Sook.

392
00:20:42,950 --> 00:20:44,180
Let's be honest.

393
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:46,080
Women like her
are fewer than 0.1 percent.

394
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:48,120
Jang Soo was lucky.

395
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:49,620
Yes.

396
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,490
The 0.1 percent.

397
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:53,820
I'll be like Jang Soo...

398
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:57,160
and find someone
that falls in that 0.1 percent.

399
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,170
What?

400
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:04,840
You've been acting suspiciously.

401
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:06,700
Are you dating?

402
00:21:07,870 --> 00:21:11,040
The smart ones catch on faster.

403
00:21:11,710 --> 00:21:13,110
- See?
- For real?

404
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:15,450
Just you wait.

405
00:21:15,450 --> 00:21:18,350
I'll introduce her to you properly.

406
00:21:21,150 --> 00:21:22,150
Gosh.

407
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:23,490
Let's have another drink.

408
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:24,550
Bye.

409
00:21:24,890 --> 00:21:26,820
- Hey.
- Wait for me.

410
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:28,430
(Pot Number 4)

411
00:21:29,930 --> 00:21:31,730
You care about being dignified,

412
00:21:31,730 --> 00:21:33,530
and you're being called
a gold digger?

413
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:35,370
Did you say a gold digger?

414
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:37,630
You mean the kind of gold digger...

415
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:40,770
who extracts money from men?

416
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:43,140
Yes. That kind of gold digger.

417
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:47,580
What does he take me for?

418
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:51,650
The more I think about it,
the worse I feel.

419
00:21:53,850 --> 00:21:55,190
Mr. Park's leaving.

420
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:57,120
He's leaving.

421
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:58,990
So what?

422
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:01,090
Get out here and see him off.

423
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,870
(Eagle Brewery)

424
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:10,970
Goodness.

425
00:22:10,970 --> 00:22:13,340
Thank you for the lovely dinner.

426
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:15,810
Your doenjang jjigae...

427
00:22:15,810 --> 00:22:18,810
is the best in Northeast Asia.

428
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,380
I'm glad it was to your liking.

429
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:24,780
You can come over
whenever you want some.

430
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:25,950
Can I really?

431
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:28,650
No. Don't come here.

432
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:30,650
Hey. Ma Kwang Sook.

433
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:34,190
My mom and I don't live here alone.

434
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:37,060
My youngest brother-in-law
lives here too.

435
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:39,930
Your mother told me so.

436
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,370
I worry what my staff will think,

437
00:22:42,370 --> 00:22:44,500
and I am afraid
of what the neighbors will say.

438
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:46,570
Please be careful.

439
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:47,770
Don't.

440
00:22:47,940 --> 00:22:49,970
If you feel that uncomfortable,

441
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:51,410
I'll stay away.

442
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:53,640
Goodbye, then, Mother.

443
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:56,910
Goodbye. Let's meet again soon.

444
00:22:56,910 --> 00:22:57,910
Sure.

445
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:06,620
Why would you meet him again?

446
00:23:06,790 --> 00:23:07,820
Be quiet.

447
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:35,450
Why are you so incredibly rude?

448
00:23:35,820 --> 00:23:38,460
How can you say that
to a guest who came to see you?

449
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,090
I never invited him over.

450
00:23:41,830 --> 00:23:44,130
He's not that bad-looking,
and he's rich.

451
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:45,900
He has no children either.

452
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:48,770
Park Sang Nam
is the best of the best.

453
00:23:49,370 --> 00:23:50,530
To be honest,

454
00:23:51,030 --> 00:23:52,570
he's way better than Jang Soo.

455
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:57,070
How dare you compare him
to someone like Jang Soo?

456
00:23:57,710 --> 00:24:00,410
Listen to yourself.
Even a dog would laugh at that.

457
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:03,780
He has the looks,
the riches, and the personality.

458
00:24:03,780 --> 00:24:06,380
Jang Soo is nothing compared to him.

459
00:24:06,620 --> 00:24:07,720
To be frank,

460
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:09,850
Jang Soo left you nothing but debt.

461
00:24:10,290 --> 00:24:11,590
He didn't leave me just debt.

462
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:13,220
He left the brewery...

463
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:14,690
and four brothers.

464
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:15,790
They're all burdens!

465
00:24:15,790 --> 00:24:17,990
They're not burdens!
They're blessings!

466
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:19,460
You imbecile.

467
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,570
How could that ever be a blessing?

468
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:26,600
I say this loud and clear.
Don't get your hopes up.

469
00:24:27,170 --> 00:24:30,510
There will be nothing
between Park Sang Nam and me.

470
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:34,210
Our deal is done.

471
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,010
I'm not pushing this for my sake.

472
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,150
For the rest of your life,

473
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:40,450
you'll be called a widow.

474
00:24:40,850 --> 00:24:42,250
That's you,

475
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:45,260
and I feel bad
that it's the life you'll live.

476
00:24:47,390 --> 00:24:48,890
Don't be this way...

477
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:50,930
to a fellow widow.

478
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:55,730
Don't pity me...

479
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:57,230
or feel bad for me,

480
00:24:57,700 --> 00:24:58,740
and let's live our lives...

481
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:01,970
with confidence and courage.

482
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:04,640
Okay?

483
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:13,650
(Eagle Brewery)

484
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:15,890
What did she just say to me?

485
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,220
Welcome.

486
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:23,330
- You're here.
- I was a little peckish...

487
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,000
and stopped by for some cup ramyeon.

488
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,530
Take a seat,
and I'll bring some over.

489
00:25:27,630 --> 00:25:29,400
Would you? Thanks.

490
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:43,410
It's about Chun Soo.

491
00:25:45,180 --> 00:25:46,450
What about him?

492
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:48,180
He's getting a divorce.

493
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:52,860
A divorce?

494
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:58,330
I wondered why his wife
suddenly flew to Korea,

495
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:01,160
but it was to sign divorce papers.

496
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,030
Really?

497
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:06,470
I don't want to gossip,

498
00:26:09,170 --> 00:26:10,770
but she has a boyfriend in the US.

499
00:26:12,540 --> 00:26:13,580
What?

500
00:26:13,580 --> 00:26:16,980
Something is bound to happen
when a married couple...

501
00:26:17,580 --> 00:26:20,050
lives apart for too long.

502
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:22,490
Hey, you're spilling the seasoning!

503
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:26,160
Gosh, I'm sorry.
I'll get you a new one right away.

504
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:27,920
Was the news too shocking?

505
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:40,900
(Areum Gosiwon)

506
00:26:42,110 --> 00:26:43,240
You're back.

507
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:45,610
- Hey.
- Is something up?

508
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,540
You don't look so well.

509
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:50,250
I haven't been able to sleep.

510
00:26:50,580 --> 00:26:51,580
- I see.
- I'm good.

511
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:55,790
Good night, then.

512
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:27,940
- Dad, let's have breakfast.
- I don't have an appetite.

513
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,110
But you skipped dinner yesterday.

514
00:28:31,210 --> 00:28:33,720
My mouth's so dry that
I can't even tell if I'm hungry.

515
00:28:34,620 --> 00:28:37,350
Are you sure nothing's up?

516
00:28:37,490 --> 00:28:38,990
I said everything was fine.

517
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:41,220
I can grab a bite at the hotel
if I'm hungry,

518
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,630
so don't be too concerned.

519
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,700
I hope you haven't forgotten
about our lunch plans today.

520
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:47,600
Lunch?

521
00:28:48,230 --> 00:28:50,400
We're meeting
Lieutenant Oh Kang Soo.

522
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:51,530
Goodness.

523
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,100
Was that today?

524
00:28:55,410 --> 00:28:57,610
Something came up at the hospital,
so Gyeol can't make it.

525
00:28:58,410 --> 00:28:59,910
I'll be at the hotel on time.

526
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:01,410
Sure thing.

527
00:29:01,410 --> 00:29:02,580
Have a good day.

528
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,790
(Chairman Han Dong Seok)

529
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,600
Five companies...

530
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,800
including Silla Brewery will submit
their products to be tasted.

531
00:29:22,570 --> 00:29:24,870
Will Eagle Brewery be present?

532
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:28,810
We already tasted theirs
the other day.

533
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:31,040
No, not for tasting.

534
00:29:31,210 --> 00:29:32,310
I was talking about CEO Ma.

535
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:34,410
Will she be here
to deliver her products?

536
00:29:34,710 --> 00:29:35,710
I'm not sure.

537
00:29:36,910 --> 00:29:38,650
I'll ask the culinary department.

538
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:45,090
Hello, Chef Baek.

539
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,720
Will CEO Ma Kwang Sook
of Eagle Brewery...

540
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,530
be here with a delivery today?

541
00:29:51,260 --> 00:29:53,230
I see. Thank you.

542
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:57,330
