00:30:35,870 --> 00:30:37,810
Now that it's warmer,

551
00:30:38,110 --> 00:30:40,440
we'll have to call the ladies
to make nuruk.

552
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,050
Due to the increase in sales,

553
00:30:42,050 --> 00:30:45,220
we might run out of it
if we're not careful.

554
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:50,320
I trust you'll decide on a good day
for that.

555
00:30:55,860 --> 00:30:57,560
Gosh, the sweet aroma.

556
00:30:59,030 --> 00:31:02,230
You've really become
a proper brewer now.

557
00:31:07,370 --> 00:31:08,710
I'll get going, Kwang Sook.

558
00:31:09,370 --> 00:31:12,440
You must be going somewhere fancy
in that nice suit.

559
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:15,210
I have a job interview
in the afternoon.

560
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:17,580
Don't let the jitters get to you
and break a leg.

561
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:21,850
It'll be their loss
if they can't see your value.

562
00:31:22,420 --> 00:31:23,950
Right. I'll get going, then.

563
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:27,420
Kang Soo.

564
00:31:28,990 --> 00:31:31,090
- Good luck.
- Same here.

565
00:31:31,860 --> 00:31:32,930
Good luck to me.

566
00:31:38,370 --> 00:31:40,200
(CEO Dokgo Tak)

567
00:31:40,870 --> 00:31:42,770
The team just left...

568
00:31:42,770 --> 00:31:45,110
for the taste test at LX Hotel.

569
00:31:46,940 --> 00:31:49,280
The test was ordered
by Chairman Han himself,

570
00:31:50,050 --> 00:31:51,580
so we'll be getting good news.

571
00:31:53,020 --> 00:31:54,280
There's no need to worry.

572
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:58,320
You and Chairman Han
go way back, don't you?

573
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:02,090
You could say we're like family.

574
00:32:02,730 --> 00:32:06,430
Our families will be connected
through our children soon.

575
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:12,000
Then, your daughter and...

576
00:32:13,740 --> 00:32:16,170
We said we'd soon settle on a date.

577
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:20,610
Then there's no need
to worry about the taste test.

578
00:32:32,060 --> 00:32:33,690
Does Se Ri have a boyfriend?

579
00:32:34,190 --> 00:32:35,360
Why would you ask that?

580
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,160
There's a client of mine...

581
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:39,500
who'd like Se Ri
as her daughter-in-law.

582
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:41,830
She's from a well-known family.

583
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:44,300
We're good.

584
00:32:44,530 --> 00:32:46,900
- Se Ri must have someone.
- Of course, she does.

585
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,740
Of course. Someone like Se Ri...

586
00:32:49,740 --> 00:32:51,910
would have plenty of men
lining up to marry her.

587
00:32:52,540 --> 00:32:54,140
Would I know the family
of this boyfriend?

588
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:00,950
But the client I mentioned
is well-mannered and classy.

589
00:33:01,650 --> 00:33:03,620
It's too good of an opportunity
to pass up.

590
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:10,830
Gosh, no. Forget it.

591
00:33:10,860 --> 00:33:13,260
Seeing how you're
refusing that family tells me...

592
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:15,400
that Se Ri's seeing someone better.

593
00:33:16,730 --> 00:33:18,870
You'll soon find out.

594
00:33:19,540 --> 00:33:20,970
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

595
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:22,240
It's been too long.

596
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,770
I was too busy to come.

597
00:33:23,870 --> 00:33:25,380
I see.
Congratulations on your wedding.

598
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:27,840
Where have I seen her before?

599
00:33:28,510 --> 00:33:30,350
She's the future wife
of Jang Je Hyeong,

600
00:33:30,350 --> 00:33:31,350
Daeheung Group's chairman.

601
00:33:31,350 --> 00:33:32,650
Let me escort you to your seat.

602
00:33:32,820 --> 00:33:34,150
That's right.

603
00:33:43,860 --> 00:33:46,160
No wonder she seemed familiar.

604
00:33:47,260 --> 00:33:49,600
She's the one idolized
by every woman...

605
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,970
in Korea these days.

606
00:33:51,130 --> 00:33:52,870
He said I could bring Ha Ni.

607
00:33:53,170 --> 00:33:54,500
His children are grown...

608
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:56,040
Don't be ridiculous!

609
00:33:56,610 --> 00:33:59,510
I was just asking
about your circumstances.

610
00:34:00,310 --> 00:34:02,410
Don't you dare mention Ha Ni again.

611
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,980
She's my daughter
and has nothing to do with you.

612
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:08,650
You and Ha Ni
have always been a part of me.

613
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,320
We'll wash your hair.

614
00:34:16,630 --> 00:34:19,060
Why would they be jealous
when she's marrying a man...

615
00:34:19,060 --> 00:34:20,860
old enough to be her father?

616
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:24,300
She's becoming the wife
of one of the top five rich men...

617
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,600
in the country.

618
00:34:26,470 --> 00:34:28,770
Putting up with the age difference
is a small price to pay.

619
00:34:29,240 --> 00:34:30,670
You think so?

620
00:34:31,970 --> 00:34:33,080
The hair treatment product
is applied.

621
00:34:33,080 --> 00:34:35,210
Please wait about 30 minutes.

622
00:34:35,210 --> 00:34:36,250
Okay.

623
00:34:48,620 --> 00:34:49,730
Spit your gum out.

624
00:34:50,330 --> 00:34:52,730
- Why?
- The snapping sound bothers me.

625
00:34:54,100 --> 00:34:55,630
But it still tastes sweet.

626
00:34:55,630 --> 00:34:57,070
I'll chew it quietly.

627
00:34:57,130 --> 00:34:58,770
Just spit it out.

628
00:34:58,770 --> 00:35:00,840
What's with the fuss?

629
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:02,210
Go ahead and spit it out.

630
00:35:03,770 --> 00:35:04,770
All right.

631
00:35:10,780 --> 00:35:12,050
I'll go and get
the hair treatment mask.

632
00:35:12,050 --> 00:35:13,520
Please wait a moment.

633
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:01,360
Let's get our hair done nicely
and go eat something delicious.

634
00:36:01,430 --> 00:36:02,600
I should go to school.

635
00:36:03,830 --> 00:36:05,370
Did you hide
something precious there?

636
00:36:05,370 --> 00:36:07,000
Why do you go to school
every time you get a chance?

637
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:10,270
I'm a student,
so I should go to school.

638
00:36:10,270 --> 00:36:11,340
What about me?

639
00:36:12,380 --> 00:36:13,710
Please move to the shampoo room.

640
00:36:15,180 --> 00:36:16,210
Okay.

641
00:36:17,580 --> 00:36:19,320
- Sorry.
- Forget it.

642
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:26,090
What on earth did you do to my hair?

643
00:36:26,690 --> 00:36:27,990
I didn't do anything.

644
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:29,990
I didn't even touch your hair.

645
00:36:30,460 --> 00:36:33,330
Then why is this thing on my hair?

646
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,730
Isn't it that you got it
before coming here?

647
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,870
Are you kidding me?

648
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:41,970
Please calm down.

649
00:36:42,310 --> 00:36:45,140
We will get rid of it
without damaging your hair.

650
00:36:45,140 --> 00:36:46,240
Please don't worry.

651
00:36:47,610 --> 00:36:50,510
I heard it would come off easily
if you used mosquito repellent.

652
00:36:52,620 --> 00:36:53,780
What did you say?

653
00:36:54,750 --> 00:36:55,950
Or not.

654
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:00,320
Darn it.

655
00:37:04,530 --> 00:37:05,700
Ha Ni.

656
00:37:06,300 --> 00:37:08,560
Let me finish the report first.

657
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:09,970
Then I'll give you food, okay?

658
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:12,700
After you eat, you'll go to Grandma,

659
00:37:12,700 --> 00:37:14,600
and I'll go to school. Okay?

660
00:37:15,340 --> 00:37:17,540
All right? That's my girl.

661
00:37:17,910 --> 00:37:19,340
I'll make it quick.

662
00:37:23,210 --> 00:37:24,210
All right.

663
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,060
You're early.

664
00:37:36,690 --> 00:37:38,060
I woke up early in the morning...

665
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:40,060
because I couldn't wait to see you.

666
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,000
Well...

667
00:37:45,070 --> 00:37:46,100
Does it look good on me?

668
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:50,170
It would've been better
if it had a real diamond...

669
00:37:50,570 --> 00:37:51,770
in the middle.

670
00:37:52,980 --> 00:37:56,680
Come on.
I prefer something simple like this.

671
00:37:57,410 --> 00:37:59,620
You're just saying that
not to make me feel small.

672
00:38:01,580 --> 00:38:03,650
What? There are no wings.

673
00:38:04,350 --> 00:38:06,060
Are you an angel without wings?

674
00:38:08,490 --> 00:38:09,530
My goodness.

675
00:38:13,700 --> 00:38:15,500
I'll finish cleaning
and start the lesson.

676
00:38:15,500 --> 00:38:17,930
No, you should get some rest.
I'll do the cleaning.

677
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:20,500
You didn't wipe the entrance,
did you?

678
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:29,610
(Gongjubuyang Shampoo)

679
00:38:29,610 --> 00:38:31,380
(G Hair Salon)

680
00:38:42,860 --> 00:38:45,900
Ms. Ji, you should get married now.

681
00:38:46,530 --> 00:38:48,760
Aren't there any good guys
around you?

682
00:38:50,030 --> 00:38:51,630
There's one.

683
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:57,310
But he's not interested in me.

684
00:38:57,740 --> 00:38:59,810
He doesn't recognize
a great woman like you?

685
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:02,650
Who's that silly guy?

686
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:04,510
There's this silly one I like.

687
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:24,270
All right. I'm done with shampooing.

688
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:34,640
Did you only use shampoo?

689
00:39:35,210 --> 00:39:37,080
It feels so soft.

690
00:39:38,180 --> 00:39:40,580
I really like the shampoo here.

691
00:39:40,580 --> 00:39:42,950
I guess your shop is famous
for a reason.

692
00:39:42,950 --> 00:39:44,050
I know, right?

693
00:39:44,750 --> 00:39:46,290
Please go back to your seat.

694
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:47,520
Okay.

695
00:39:55,060 --> 00:39:56,070
My gosh.

696
00:39:56,730 --> 00:39:59,240
You just blow-dried my hair,
but it's so bouncy.

697
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,800
What's your secret?

698
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:03,470
Tell me.

699
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,880
It's my secret.

700
00:40:09,950 --> 00:40:10,950
(Detective Choi Sherlock)

701
00:40:11,010 --> 00:40:14,420
It's an urgent call.
Please excuse me.

702
00:40:14,420 --> 00:40:16,250
Go ahead and take your time.

703
00:40:19,050 --> 00:40:21,820
Yes, Detective.
Did you find something?

704
00:40:28,100 --> 00:40:29,630
(G Hair Salon)

705
00:40:29,630 --> 00:40:34,140
(Choi Sherlock Detective Agency)

706
00:40:44,450 --> 00:40:45,650
That was quick.

707
00:40:46,020 --> 00:40:47,720
I didn't even close my store.

708
00:40:47,720 --> 00:40:49,350
I just came running in a heartbeat.

709
00:40:50,890 --> 00:40:53,060
So you found the crucial clue?

710
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:56,430
Please have a seat first.

711
00:40:56,530 --> 00:40:57,690
Okay.

712
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:12,940
Please don't hesitate
and just get to the point.

713
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:20,850
In a nutshell, Ms. Kim...

714
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:28,590
is living a double life.

715
00:41:34,530 --> 00:41:36,270
Legally, she's single,

716
00:41:36,630 --> 00:41:38,300
but she has a ten-year-old daughter.

717
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:41,140
In the family register,
she is listed as her sister.

718
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:44,710
Her father is the leader
of Oseong Gang,

719
00:41:44,710 --> 00:41:46,480
a nationwide criminal organization,

720
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:49,180
and he's currently imprisoned
in Uijeongbu Prison.

721
00:41:49,380 --> 00:41:52,650
(Angel Piano)

722
00:41:52,650 --> 00:41:53,750
I knew it.

723
00:41:54,980 --> 00:41:56,490
My hunch was right.

724
00:42:02,660 --> 00:42:04,430
(Angel Piano)

725
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,200
Oh, no.

726
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:10,300
This is not it.

727
00:42:11,170 --> 00:42:12,170
Again.

728
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:14,340
Stop it.

729
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:16,270
Try it again.

730
00:42:43,100 --> 00:42:45,000
(Be happy here and now.)

731
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:54,440
This is Silla Brewery's new product,

732
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:55,950
Sorabol's Moonlit Night.

733
00:43:10,660 --> 00:43:13,660
This is the taste test report
from the executives.

734
00:43:14,860 --> 00:43:16,270
Silla Brewery's product...

735
00:43:17,200 --> 00:43:18,830
got a lower score than expected.

736
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:22,600
Products from other companies
also failed to meet...

737
00:43:22,940 --> 00:43:25,710
our executives' requirements
as they had little time to prepare.

738
00:43:26,240 --> 00:43:27,310
Is that so?

739
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:32,480
Then let's select
Eagle Brewery's product.

740
00:43:33,050 --> 00:43:34,550
Yes, sir. We'll do that.

741
00:43:37,620 --> 00:43:40,360
(Chairman Han Dong Seok)

742
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:56,570
Hello?

743
00:43:57,070 --> 00:43:59,310
It's LX Hotel's Han Dong Seok.

744
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,810
What made you want to call?

745
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:03,950
You'll soon hear from the person
in charge,

746
00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:07,880
but I called ahead
to give you the good news.

747
00:44:10,450 --> 00:44:11,690
"Good news?"

748
00:44:11,890 --> 00:44:13,860
Yes. I have good news.

749
00:44:15,260 --> 00:44:17,790
Did you figure out the person...

750
00:44:18,190 --> 00:44:19,500
who called me a gold digger?

751
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:24,470
About yesterday...
That was my mistake.

752
00:44:24,530 --> 00:44:26,500
I apologize sincerely.

753
00:44:27,070 --> 00:44:30,070
Did you confirm the name
of the guest in Room 1512?

754
00:44:31,710 --> 00:44:34,480
Yes. I won't make any excuses.

755
00:44:34,710 --> 00:44:35,740
I'm sorry.

756
00:44:37,250 --> 00:44:39,150
Since you apologized,

757
00:44:39,650 --> 00:44:42,520
I'll be cool and accept it.

758
00:44:43,220 --> 00:44:44,220
Goodbye.

759
00:44:45,220 --> 00:44:46,560
Wait.

760
00:44:50,130 --> 00:44:51,690
I have good news.

761
00:44:52,490 --> 00:44:54,960
For the festival that's coming up
in a few days,

762
00:44:56,470 --> 00:44:58,770
we've decided to serve
Eagle Brewery's makgeolli...

763
00:44:59,770 --> 00:45:01,370
with our food.

764
00:45:02,470 --> 00:45:03,610
Good.

765
00:45:04,610 --> 00:45:05,670
"Good."

766
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:08,980
Is that all you have to say?

767
00:45:09,980 --> 00:45:11,010
What?

768
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:13,320
Do I need to say more?

769
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:16,190
No. Not at all.

770
00:45:16,190 --> 00:45:17,490
I hope...

771
00:45:17,490 --> 00:45:20,220
you prepare well
and get a good response.

772
00:45:21,090 --> 00:45:22,090
Okay.

773
00:45:22,860 --> 00:45:24,890
I'll prepare as best I can.

774
00:45:29,330 --> 00:45:30,830
She has no manners.

775
00:45:32,500 --> 00:45:34,940
I was considerate enough
to call her myself.

776
00:45:35,270 --> 00:45:36,270
"Good."

777
00:45:37,070 --> 00:45:38,170
What was that?

778
00:45:41,010 --> 00:45:42,850
My goodness.

779
00:45:48,180 --> 00:45:50,020
Mr. Go. Kim.

780
00:45:50,390 --> 00:45:52,420
- What is it?
- Is something wrong?

781
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:56,760
The festival people
decided to serve our makgeolli!

782
00:45:57,330 --> 00:45:58,560
That's it?

783
00:45:58,560 --> 00:46:00,600
You made a fuss
about what I knew would happen.

784
00:46:04,100 --> 00:46:07,000
I heard that Silla Brewery
and other big companies...

785
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:08,740
sent in samples to compete.

786
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:10,540
I felt a bit intimidated.

787
00:46:10,610 --> 00:46:13,880
Don't compare our product
with Silla Brewery's cheap stuff.

788
00:46:13,880 --> 00:46:15,180
That's nonsense.

789
00:46:16,150 --> 00:46:19,280
Shouldn't we eat out
to celebrate something like this?

790
00:46:19,380 --> 00:46:22,050
You bet we should.
Name what you want. It's on me.

791
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:24,120
Ask for beef.

792
00:46:24,350 --> 00:46:25,350
Beef.

793
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,420
Beef? Okay.

794
00:46:27,820 --> 00:46:29,790
We should eat that. Let's go.

795
00:46:31,060 --> 00:46:32,160
Darn you.

796
00:46:32,390 --> 00:46:35,030
How could you ruin it
at the last minute?

797
00:46:35,260 --> 00:46:37,570
I had Chairman Han's word.

798
00:46:37,770 --> 00:46:39,900
What on earth did you do...

799
00:46:39,900 --> 00:46:42,000
that we got such horrible results?

800
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:44,540
We didn't have enough time
to develop the product...

801
00:46:44,540 --> 00:46:46,840
and failed to find
the ideal ratio of taste...

802
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:48,480
- and flavor...
- You fool.

803
00:46:48,580 --> 00:46:50,610
Do you call that an excuse?

804
00:46:51,210 --> 00:46:52,250
I'm sorry, sir.

805
00:46:52,810 --> 00:46:55,550
Those punks in the Development Team.

806
00:46:55,550 --> 00:46:57,390
I'll fire them all.

807
00:46:57,790 --> 00:46:59,920
They're treated too well
and have gotten too comfortable.

808
00:47:00,020 --> 00:47:02,420
They don't take
their jobs seriously.

809
00:47:04,230 --> 00:47:05,230
And you.

810
00:47:05,590 --> 00:47:08,300
Why can't you keep a tight rein
on the staff?

811
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:10,470
What do you even do here?

812
00:47:11,370 --> 00:47:12,370
I'm sorry, sir.

813
00:47:12,370 --> 00:47:14,870
Is that the only thing you can say?

814
00:47:15,070 --> 00:47:16,100
I'm sor...

815
00:47:16,870 --> 00:47:19,340
Forget it. Get out of here!

816
00:47:19,340 --> 00:47:20,840
I can't stand your face!

817
00:47:23,780 --> 00:47:26,580
My gosh. This is so annoying!

818
00:47:27,220 --> 00:47:30,290
I'd curse him out if our kids
weren't going to get married.

819
00:47:32,090 --> 00:47:33,120
It's okay.

820
00:47:33,520 --> 00:47:35,520
Dokgo Tak. You're doing well.

821
00:47:35,990 --> 00:47:39,800
Relax. Calm down.

822
00:47:52,270 --> 00:47:53,880
Hello, Mr. Dokgo.

823
00:47:54,710 --> 00:47:57,880
Hello. I just heard the news.

824
00:47:58,950 --> 00:48:02,050
Our Silla Brewery's product
didn't make the cut...

825
00:48:02,350 --> 00:48:03,920
to be served at the festival?

826
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:05,590
(Chairman Han Dong Seok)

827
00:48:05,590 --> 00:48:08,490
That's a great shame.

828
00:48:09,390 --> 00:48:10,990
It was an official tasting,

829
00:48:10,990 --> 00:48:13,960
so even as the chairman,
I couldn't change the results.

830
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:17,870
I'm sure that was the case.

831
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:20,570
You don't need to worry.

832
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:24,570
Could you tell me which product...

833
00:48:24,970 --> 00:48:27,240
made the final cut to be served?

834
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:31,050
Jang-Kwang Makgeolli
from Eagle Brewery.

835
00:48:32,010 --> 00:48:33,280
That's what we'll be serving.

836
00:48:33,950 --> 00:48:35,280
Jang-Kwang...

837
00:48:37,420 --> 00:48:38,520
Jang...

838
00:48:40,220 --> 00:48:42,020
Jang-Kwang Makgeolli?

839
00:48:42,360 --> 00:48:46,060
I thought I told you
about the tasteless rumors...

840
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:49,500
that were circulating
about Eagle Brewery.

841
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:52,030
I tipped you off.

842
00:48:52,230 --> 00:48:53,970
Rumors are rumors,

843
00:48:53,970 --> 00:48:56,440
and good wine tastes good.

844
00:48:57,370 --> 00:49:00,280
Since you didn't get
the result you wanted,

845
00:49:00,440 --> 00:49:03,350
let me treat you to a meal
to console you.

846
00:49:08,250 --> 00:49:09,320
Shoot.

847
00:49:11,890 --> 00:49:13,690
Darn it!

848
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:16,930
Eagle...

849
00:49:16,930 --> 00:49:18,890
Eagle!

850
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:24,500
Who on earth are they to me
that they keep tackling me?

851
00:49:28,870 --> 00:49:29,940
This won't do.

852
00:49:31,140 --> 00:49:34,610
I'll chew them out
and stomp all over them...

853
00:49:35,480 --> 00:49:37,680
so they're left without a trace.

854
00:49:38,810 --> 00:49:40,320
That woman earlier.

855
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:43,320
The woman who'll marry
Daeheung Group's chairman.

856
00:49:44,150 --> 00:49:45,350
What about her?

857
00:49:47,390 --> 00:49:50,090
Did you stick
the chewing gum to her hair?

858
00:49:50,860 --> 00:49:52,230
You offered...

859
00:49:52,230 --> 00:49:54,130
to throw away the gum I was chewing.

860
00:49:55,230 --> 00:49:56,230
It wasn't you, was it?

861
00:49:58,570 --> 00:49:59,570
I can't say.

862
00:50:02,070 --> 00:50:04,910
It's either yes or no.
Why can't you say?

863
00:50:06,610 --> 00:50:07,680
It was you.

864
00:50:09,140 --> 00:50:11,250
Did you stick the gum on her hair?

865
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:16,520
- Yes.
- My gosh.

866
00:50:17,650 --> 00:50:18,890
I don't believe it.

867
00:50:19,820 --> 00:50:22,590
Why did you do such a thing?

868
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:23,890
Why?

869
00:50:26,400 --> 00:50:27,530
She's annoying.

870
00:50:28,860 --> 00:50:30,130
Why is she annoying?

871
00:50:30,370 --> 00:50:32,600
She cares too much about money.

872
00:50:32,900 --> 00:50:34,300
I couldn't stand it.

873
00:50:36,270 --> 00:50:37,970
Dokgo Se Ri.

874
00:50:38,070 --> 00:50:41,810
Why do you care
what she thinks about money?

875
00:50:41,910 --> 00:50:43,780
She has nothing to do with you.

876
00:50:44,410 --> 00:50:46,250
I just felt like doing it.

877
00:50:46,420 --> 00:50:48,650
You could get into huge trouble.

878
00:50:49,420 --> 00:50:51,250
What if someone saw?

879
00:50:51,250 --> 00:50:52,850
What if there were cameras?

880
00:50:53,220 --> 00:50:55,720
I knew there weren't any
and moved in and out fast.

881
00:50:56,660 --> 00:50:57,960
My gosh.

882
00:51:01,700 --> 00:51:03,370
It's not funny.

883
00:51:03,600 --> 00:51:05,330
Why are you acting out of character?

884
00:51:11,770 --> 00:51:12,840
You really...

885
00:51:26,460 --> 00:51:28,020
We need to talk later.

886
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:29,990
What for?

887
00:51:30,430 --> 00:51:32,690
You've been acting strangely.

888
00:51:33,600 --> 00:51:35,360
You're not my darling puppy.

889
00:51:36,470 --> 00:51:38,030
I'll get a facial at the hotel...

890
00:51:38,030 --> 00:51:39,400
and pick you up on time.

891
00:51:39,670 --> 00:51:41,200
I'll be late. I have a meeting.

892
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:43,270
Why do you always have a meeting?

893
00:51:43,740 --> 00:51:45,740
Are you the only TA
in your department?

894
00:51:46,840 --> 00:51:48,780
That's how good your daughter is.

895
00:51:49,110 --> 00:51:50,180
You can go.

896
00:51:51,280 --> 00:51:52,310
Goodness.

897
00:51:55,050 --> 00:51:56,690
What got into her these days?

898
00:52:05,090 --> 00:52:06,330
Professor.

899
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:08,660
How are you?

900
00:52:10,200 --> 00:52:12,600
You seem to be in a good mood.
Did you get good news?

901
00:52:14,300 --> 00:52:16,340
It's not exactly good news.

902
00:52:16,510 --> 00:52:18,070
More like
something refreshing happened.

903
00:52:18,970 --> 00:52:19,980
What's that?

904
00:52:20,210 --> 00:52:22,040
Will it cheer me up too?

905
00:52:23,410 --> 00:52:26,180
There was a person
I was annoyed with,

906
00:52:26,550 --> 00:52:28,480
but I taught her
a small lesson today.

907
00:52:29,280 --> 00:52:30,420
"A small lesson?"

908
00:52:31,990 --> 00:52:34,860
You'll probably tell me off
if I tell you the details.

909
00:52:35,890 --> 00:52:36,930
It's a secret.

910
00:52:38,660 --> 00:52:40,560
You can be an oddball.

911
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:44,700
Whatever it is,
if it cheered you up, it's good.

912
00:52:52,110 --> 00:52:53,780
Hello, welcome.

913
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:55,510
Goodness.

914
00:52:57,810 --> 00:52:59,310
How are you?

915
00:52:59,580 --> 00:53:01,050
It has been a while.

916
00:53:01,050 --> 00:53:03,520
It has. Have you been busy?

917
00:53:03,590 --> 00:53:06,390
I had so much to do,
I couldn't visit.

918
00:53:07,320 --> 00:53:09,620
But I bring good news.

919
00:53:10,760 --> 00:53:12,330
Good news?

920
00:53:12,630 --> 00:53:15,300
You mentioned
Eagle Brewery last time.

921
00:53:15,500 --> 00:53:16,600
Oh, right.

922
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,530
You said you'd call
after reviewing the files.

923
00:53:19,530 --> 00:53:21,940
I had given up
since I wasn't contacted.

924
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:24,410
The purchase department just called.

925
00:53:24,740 --> 00:53:27,210
You're to present the product
at the head office next week.

926
00:53:27,980 --> 00:53:29,080
Really?

927
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:30,110
Yes.

928
00:53:31,710 --> 00:53:34,850
I had given up
since I didn't hear back from you.

929
00:53:35,150 --> 00:53:36,480
No way.

930
00:53:37,550 --> 00:53:40,660
Thank you so much. Thank you.

931
00:53:41,490 --> 00:53:43,690
- Goodness. Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

932
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:45,160
My gosh.

933
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:50,670
(Mi Sun)

934
00:54:05,210 --> 00:54:07,580
The call cannot be connected and
will be transferred to voicemail.

935
00:54:07,580 --> 00:54:08,750
He's not picking up.

936
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:16,190
I have good news.

937
00:54:16,690 --> 00:54:18,260
Call me when you have time.

938
00:54:31,010 --> 00:54:32,540
Goodness, it's Bom.

939
00:54:33,240 --> 00:54:34,240
Hey...

940
00:54:39,310 --> 00:54:40,320
What?

941
00:54:41,420 --> 00:54:42,820
It's been a while, Bom.

942
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:44,420
Have you been well?

943
00:54:45,450 --> 00:54:48,290
Gyeol only told me a few days ago
that you had left the navy.

944
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:50,590
I'm afraid it happened that way.

945
00:54:58,500 --> 00:55:00,800
Something urgent came up
at the hospital, so Gyeol...

946
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:03,240
Right. We talked
on the phone just now.

947
00:55:04,270 --> 00:55:06,240
My dad's waiting for us
at the restaurant.

948
00:55:06,240 --> 00:55:07,740
- Let's go.
- Sure.

949
00:55:08,440 --> 00:55:09,680
Just a second.

950
00:55:34,700 --> 00:55:35,700
Thank you.

951
00:55:35,840 --> 00:55:36,840
Goodness.

952
00:55:38,040 --> 00:55:39,710
Hello, I'm Oh Kang Soo.

953
00:55:40,580 --> 00:55:41,580
It's a pleasure to meet you.

954
00:55:43,080 --> 00:55:44,110
Let's sit.

955
00:55:50,020 --> 00:55:52,020
I hope I didn't take time
out of your busy schedule.

956
00:55:52,620 --> 00:55:53,690
Of course not.

957
00:55:54,190 --> 00:55:56,390
Gyeol told me you left the navy.

958
00:55:56,790 --> 00:55:58,660
That's right.
Due to an issue with my ears,

959
00:55:58,660 --> 00:56:00,460
I couldn't manage
underwater training.

960
00:56:01,830 --> 00:56:03,130
Does it affect your daily life?

961
00:56:03,260 --> 00:56:04,530
Not at all.

962
00:56:05,270 --> 00:56:07,570
You'll have to look for
something new to do.

963
00:56:08,140 --> 00:56:10,610
I'm afraid so.
I've been looking for a job...

964
00:56:10,610 --> 00:56:12,170
while helping my sister-in-law
at her brewery.

965
00:56:13,010 --> 00:56:14,110
Her what?

966
00:56:14,710 --> 00:56:17,550
It's a place
that brews alcoholic beverages.

967
00:56:18,050 --> 00:56:20,380
I see. Like one
that brews makgeolli?

968
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:21,920
That's right.

969
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:24,820
It's been in the family
since my grandfather,

970
00:56:24,820 --> 00:56:26,760
but my eldest brother
passed away recently,

971
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:28,760
so my sister-in-law
has been running it since.

972
00:56:31,390 --> 00:56:32,630
Hold on.

973
00:56:33,390 --> 00:56:34,960
Is the name of the brewery...

974
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:36,600
It's Eagle Brewery.

975
00:56:37,100 --> 00:56:38,830
Eagle Brewery?

976
00:56:40,270 --> 00:56:41,600
Do you know the place?

977
00:56:43,140 --> 00:56:44,570
Yes, of course.

978
00:56:45,010 --> 00:56:47,440
The brewery supplies us
with traditional wine.

979
00:56:52,210 --> 00:56:53,210
I see.

980
00:56:55,280 --> 00:56:57,750
My father's the chairman
of this hotel, you see.

981
00:56:59,750 --> 00:57:00,790
Really?

982
00:57:04,360 --> 00:57:06,530
Please think fondly
of my sister-in-law.

983
00:57:09,860 --> 00:57:12,830
Did your sister-in-law
say anything about me?

984
00:57:13,200 --> 00:57:14,200
No, sir.

985
00:57:14,870 --> 00:57:17,610
She only said she was
supplying makgeolli to the hotel.

986
00:57:18,040 --> 00:57:19,040
I see.

987
00:57:25,450 --> 00:57:27,550
Running a brewery won't be easy...

988
00:57:27,550 --> 00:57:30,190
because it requires real expertise.

989
00:57:31,350 --> 00:57:35,120
How did your sister-in-law
get to run the brewery?

990
00:57:36,490 --> 00:57:39,230
Since the brewery
was my late brother's dream...

991
00:57:39,760 --> 00:57:41,000
and the root of our family,

992
00:57:42,330 --> 00:57:45,070
she couldn't let us abandon
the family business for generations.

993
00:57:45,300 --> 00:57:46,770
That's why she took the brewery over
on our behalf.

994
00:57:49,070 --> 00:57:51,410
There could've been an issue...

995
00:57:51,410 --> 00:57:53,980
regarding the inheritance
among family members.

996
00:57:56,540 --> 00:57:59,150
It was sitting on a pile of debt,
so my brothers and I were ready...

997
00:57:59,150 --> 00:58:00,750
to give up the inheritance
and dissolve it.

998
00:58:01,850 --> 00:58:03,050
But my sister-in-law spent...

999
00:58:03,050 --> 00:58:05,020
her severance pay and even used
her mother's retirement savings.

1000
00:58:05,690 --> 00:58:08,390
She also took out a loan
through her previous job,

1001
00:58:08,390 --> 00:58:10,160
which was just enough
to keep the brewery afloat.

1002
00:58:13,060 --> 00:58:14,800
Gosh, I see.

1003
00:58:15,730 --> 00:58:18,230
My brothers and I
have been deeply grateful to her.

1004
00:58:18,700 --> 00:58:21,970
We respect and rely on her
as if she were our big sister.

1005
00:58:23,840 --> 00:58:24,840
She's the one...

1006
00:58:26,210 --> 00:58:28,210
I respect the most in this world.

1007
00:58:52,900 --> 00:58:55,370
The call cannot be connected and
will be transferred to voicemail.

1008
00:58:56,140 --> 00:58:57,970
Who are you calling
in the middle of eating?

1009
00:58:59,410 --> 00:59:02,540
Chun Soo.
I was wondering if he had eaten.

1010
00:59:05,610 --> 00:59:07,450
Try worrying about your own mother
like that.

1011
00:59:08,350 --> 00:59:11,390
How come you're worried about him?
He's not even family by blood.

1012
00:59:12,450 --> 00:59:13,760
I feel bad for him.

1013
00:59:14,190 --> 00:59:16,590
He had to live alone
and send money abroad for ten years,

1014
00:59:16,590 --> 00:59:18,130
but his wife cheated on him.

1015
00:59:18,530 --> 00:59:20,430
Don't worry about others
and worry about yourself,

1016
00:59:20,430 --> 00:59:21,760
Ma Kwang Sook.

1017
00:59:22,230 --> 00:59:23,560
I'm doing well for myself.

1018
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:27,100
You and Park Sang Nam...

1019
00:59:27,100 --> 00:59:28,200
Again?

1020
00:59:28,600 --> 00:59:31,610
What did I say about
bringing him up?

1021
00:59:33,370 --> 00:59:35,540
Why am I not even allowed
to talk about him?

1022
00:59:35,940 --> 00:59:37,510
Fine, you brat.

1023
00:59:46,650 --> 00:59:48,860
Sighing in the middle of a meal
will only chase luck away.

1024
00:59:49,890 --> 00:59:51,490
It's Heung Soo.

1025
00:59:52,330 --> 00:59:54,730
I'm worried about how he's doing.

1026
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:57,430
Unbelievable. Just unbelievable.

1027
00:59:58,100 --> 01:00:00,030
Get a grip on yourself, you brat!

1028
01:00:00,600 --> 01:00:01,870
I bet you thought I'd smack you.

1029
01:00:21,890 --> 01:00:25,690
(I have good news!
Call me when you have time.)

1030
01:00:25,690 --> 01:00:27,130
Is he busy?

1031
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:35,670
Could something be up?

1032
01:00:45,250 --> 01:00:47,320
(Room 303, Areum Gosiwon)

1033
01:00:47,450 --> 01:00:48,720
Are you kidding me?

1034
01:00:50,750 --> 01:00:51,790
Hey, you!

1035
01:00:52,420 --> 01:00:53,420
Yes?

1036
01:00:54,290 --> 01:00:55,290
Get over here.

1037
01:00:56,890 --> 01:00:58,190
Room 303.

1038
01:00:58,530 --> 01:01:01,300
His phone has been ringing
since last night.

1039
01:01:02,130 --> 01:01:04,170
Check if everything's all right.

1040
01:01:10,000 --> 01:01:11,040
Mr. Oh?

1041
01:01:12,340 --> 01:01:13,570
Are you in there?

1042
01:01:16,010 --> 01:01:17,110
Aren't you there?

1043
01:01:18,310 --> 01:01:19,450
I don't know.

1044
01:01:19,480 --> 01:01:21,220
- Let yourself in.
- Darn.

1045
01:01:22,320 --> 01:01:23,850
I'm coming in.

1046
01:01:28,520 --> 01:01:29,560
Mr. Oh?

1047
01:01:31,730 --> 01:01:33,330
Mr. Oh, are you asleep?

1048
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:41,200
This is a prescription bottle.

1049
01:01:41,840 --> 01:01:42,900
What's this?

1050
01:01:44,510 --> 01:01:47,210
Mr. Oh, wake up.

1051
01:01:47,210 --> 01:01:48,280
Mr. Oh?

1052
01:01:49,810 --> 01:01:51,650
Hey, call an ambulance.

1053
01:01:51,650 --> 01:01:53,820
- Call for help right now!
- My goodness.

1054
01:01:54,180 --> 01:01:55,320
An ambulance...

1055
01:01:56,820 --> 01:01:57,820
Hello?

1056
01:01:59,490 --> 01:02:01,660
Isn't this Oh Chun Soo's phone?

1057
01:02:02,490 --> 01:02:04,360
Mr. Oh is unconscious.

1058
01:02:04,360 --> 01:02:05,990
It looks like he took some pills.

1059
01:02:06,860 --> 01:02:07,860
What?

1060
01:02:08,600 --> 01:02:09,730
What did you just say?

1061
01:02:14,070 --> 01:02:15,940
(Emergency Medical Center)

1062
01:02:17,440 --> 01:02:18,970
(Emergency Medical Center)

1063
01:02:18,970 --> 01:02:20,370
(Ambulance)

1064
01:02:23,380 --> 01:02:24,410
(For ambulances only)

1065
01:02:26,550 --> 01:02:27,980
A male patient in his 40s.

1066
01:02:27,980 --> 01:02:29,820
Suspected overdose
of benzodiazepine.

1067
01:02:29,820 --> 01:02:31,950
Decreased pulse and blood pressure.

1068
01:02:31,950 --> 01:02:33,090
Due to weak spontaneous breathing,

1069
01:02:33,090 --> 01:02:35,190
assisted breathing is being provided
using a BVM.

1070
01:02:35,320 --> 01:02:36,790
Sure. Check his vitals.

1071
01:02:36,790 --> 01:02:37,790
Yes, doctor.

1072
01:02:51,310 --> 01:02:54,310
(119 Emergency Medical Services)

1073
01:03:39,550 --> 01:03:42,060
(For Eagle Brothers)

1074
01:03:42,290 --> 01:03:43,690
It's bad, Beom Soo.

1075
01:03:43,960 --> 01:03:46,530
Chun Soo took sleeping pills
and was taken to the ER.

1076
01:03:46,760 --> 01:03:48,130
What about Chun Soo?

1077
01:03:48,200 --> 01:03:49,760
There's no time for this.

1078
01:03:49,760 --> 01:03:51,470
I think you should go.

1079
01:03:51,670 --> 01:03:52,930
Did I get him drunk?

1080
01:03:53,130 --> 01:03:55,270
Why are you blaming me for it?

1081
01:03:55,400 --> 01:03:57,710
I get that you're angry and upset,
Heung Soo,

1082
01:03:57,710 --> 01:04:00,840
but you can't speak rudely
or resort to violence.

1083
01:04:01,210 --> 01:04:04,150
Find out
Eagle Brewery's biggest weakness.

1084
01:04:04,280 --> 01:04:05,880
Whether it's money or people,

1085
01:04:05,880 --> 01:04:08,550
do whatever it takes
to find out how to deal them...

1086
01:04:08,750 --> 01:04:10,050
the deadliest blow.
